The paper deals with the construction of light spanners and SLTs in distributed settings, which are fundamental problems in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves graph algorithms and network construction, which suggest cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses the CONGEST model, which is a popular model for distributed computing over networks, indicating cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another possible category.
